# Build context is the repo root (Dockerfile at apps/web/Dockerfile). The image
# does a fresh `pnpm install`, so none of these are needed in the context — and
# excluding them keeps the ACR upload small.
**/node_modules
.git
.gitignore
**/.next
**/.expo
.claude
**/coverage
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/*.log
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
# infra/ holds Terraform (tfvars, tfvars.json, auto.tfvars, tfstate, plans,
# override.tf — all secret-bearing) and is NEVER needed by the web image build
# context (the Dockerfile only copies package manifests, apps/, packages/). Exclude
# it WHOLESALE so `az acr build .` can't upload any infra secret file — this kills
# the entire class of "missed Terraform secret variant" at once.
infra/
**/infra/
# Defense-in-depth: also exclude Terraform/secret artifacts anywhere else (harmless
# overlap with infra/ above; catches stray files outside the infra tree).
**/.terraform/
**/*.tfstate*
**/*.tfplan
**/tfplan
**/*.tfvars
**/*.tfvars.json
**/.DS_Store
